PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1776791154
OL,3,CInquiry: Prosecuting criminals with
OL,4,Cmental illness should be 'default'
OL,6,FThe case was not referred to the Crown
OL,7,FProsecution Service after the
OL,8,Fsupervising officer, sergeant Katie
OL,9,FSparks, read a doctor's email which
OL,10,Fsaid Calocane was "not in touch with
OL,11,Freality", the inquiry previously heard.
OL,13,FMs Sparks told the inquiry that, on
OL,14,Freflection, police could have done
OL,15,Fmore, like speaking to the doctor
OL,16,Fabout the case and questioning
OL,17,FCalocane further before closing the
OL,18,Finvestigation.
OL,26,@rD@SOUsD@HO]
